radxa-penta-fan-ctrl (1.0.2-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Add hardware PWM channel configuration support:
    - New PWMCHAN environment variable for selecting PWM channel (pwm0/pwm1/pwm2/pwm3)
    - Enables use of GPIO13 (PWM0_CHAN1) on Raspberry Pi 5 for hardware PWM
    - Improved logging shows both chip and channel (e.g., pwmchip0/pwm1)
  * Critical bug fix:
    - Fixed PWM period file opened in read mode but code tried to write
    - This bug prevented hardware PWM initialization on all platforms
  * Hardware PWM optimization:
    - True 25 kHz hardware PWM for Noctua and other PC PWM fans
    - Eliminates software PWM thread (reduces from 4 to 1 task)
    - Zero CPU overhead for PWM generation
  * Raspberry Pi 5 hardware modification instructions:
    - Move the 35Ω resistor below the top hat connector on the bottom layer
      to the right free spot
    - Device tree overlay required: dtoverlay=pwm-2chan,pin2=13,func2=4
    - Must use 4-pin PWM fan (recommended: Noctua NF-A4x10 5V PWM)
    - Do NOT use the tach line of the original fan header
  * Configuration for Raspberry Pi 5 with hardware mod:
    - HARDWARE_PWM=1, PWMCHIP=0, PWMCHAN=1
    - This provides hardware-accelerated fan control at 25 kHz

 -- Francisco Javier Acosta Padilla <fco.ja.ac@gmail.com>  Tue, 17 Feb 2026 12:24:00 +0100

radxa-penta-fan-ctrl (1.0.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Optimize CPU usage and reduce heat generation:
    - Reduce software PWM frequency from 25 kHz to 500 Hz (prevents excessive CPU toggling)
    - Implement adaptive SSD info polling (reduces smartctl overhead)
    - Fixed config file whitespace parsing for proper OLED rotation setting
  * Performance improvements while maintaining thermal control accuracy

 -- Francisco Javier Acosta Padilla <fco.ja.ac@gmail.com>  Sat, 25 Oct 2025 23:15:44 +0200

radxa-penta-fan-ctrl (1.0.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial Release
  * Fan control daemon for Penta SATA HAT top board
  * Smart thermal control with asymmetric ramping and trend analysis
  * Cooldown hold mechanism to prevent rapid fan off cycles
  * Temperature-based fan speed control with configurable thresholds
  * OLED display with system info, disk temps, and RAID status
  * Hardware and software PWM support (25 kHz frequency)
  * Two-level debug logging (RADXA_DEBUG=1 for normal, =2 for verbose)
  * Compatible with Raspberry Pi 4/5, ROCK Pi, and other boards

 -- Francisco Javier Acosta Padilla <fco.ja.ac@gmail.com>  Wed, 22 Oct 2025 00:00:00 +0000
